# ============================================
# .gitignore — this file tells Git "don't track these files"
# Think of it like a note on a box that says "don't pack this."
# ============================================

# --- Operating system junk files ---
# Windows creates this file in folders you look at in File Explorer
Thumbs.db
ehthumbs.db
Desktop.ini

# macOS creates this file in folders you look at in Finder
.DS_Store
.AppleDouble
.LSOverride

# Linux file manager leftovers
.directory
.Trash-*

# --- Editor / IDE folders ---
# VS Code settings some people don't want shared
.vscode/
# JetBrains IDEs (WebStorm, IntelliJ, etc.)
.idea/
# Sublime Text project files
*.sublime-workspace
*.sublime-project

# --- Node.js stuff ---
# This is dev-only test tooling (Vitest, for the pure logic in
# logic.js) — the real, deployed site still has zero dependencies
# and zero build step. "node_modules" is where npm downloads every
# package to (huge, and easy to redownload with "npm install"), so
# it never needs to be tracked by Git. "package-lock.json" is the
# opposite — small, and IS tracked on purpose (see below) so
# everyone gets the exact same versions of everything.
node_modules/
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*

# --- Logs and temp files ---
*.log
*.tmp
*.temp
*.bak
*.swp

# --- Environment / secret files ---
# Just in case a mail service, form backend, or API key ever gets added later
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local